Windows Visual Studio Code shortcuts

- Ctrl + P: Quick Open
- Ctrl + Shift + P: Show All Commands
- Ctrl + Shift + O: Go to Symbol
- Ctrl + Shift + M: Show Problems
- Ctrl + Shift + D: Open Run and Debug
- Ctrl + B: Toggle Sidebar
- Ctrl + J: Toggle Panel
- Ctrl + `: Toggle Integrated Terminal
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + S: Keyboard Shortcuts
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + X: Trim Trailing Whitespace
- Ctrl + /: Toggle Line Comment
- Shift + Alt + A: Toggle Block Comment
- Shift + Alt + F: Format Document
- Ctrl + Shift + K: Delete Line
- Ctrl + Enter: Insert Line Below
- Ctrl + Shift + Enter: Insert Line Above
- Alt + Up / Alt + Down: Move Line Up/Down
- Shift + Alt + Up / Shift + Alt + Down: Copy Line Up/Down
- Ctrl + D: Add Selection to Next Find Match
- Ctrl + L: Select Line
- Ctrl + F: Find
- Ctrl + H: Replace
- Ctrl + Shift + H: Replace in Files
- Ctrl + F2: Select All Occurrences of Find Match
- Ctrl + Shift + \: Jump to Matching Bracket
- F11: Toggle Full Screen
- Ctrl + W: Close Editor
- Ctrl + Shift + T: Reopen Closed Editor
- Ctrl + N: New File
- Ctrl + S: Save File
- Ctrl + K, S: Keyboard Shortcuts
- Ctrl + Shift + E: Show Explorer
- Ctrl + Shift + F: Find in Files
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + 0: Focus into Editor Group 0

JavaScript-specific shortcuts

- F12: Go to Definition
- Alt + F12: Peek Definition
- Ctrl + .: Quick Fix
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + I: Show Hover
- Ctrl + K, M: Change Language Mode
- F2: Rename Symbol
- Alt + Click: Multi-cursor
- Ctrl + Shift + `: Create New Integrated Terminal
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + U: Change All Occurrences to Uppercase
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + L: Change All Occurrences to Lowercase
- Ctrl + Shift + Space: Trigger Parameter Hints
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + 8: Toggle Problems Panel
- Ctrl + K, Ctrl + /: Toggle Line Comment for selected JS code
